Defines the linkage of the product sensors 1 and 2 with respect to the trigger signal. 0 = Off, 1 = AND Operation (both sensors must recieve a signal), 2 = OR operation (only one sensor have to recieve a signal)
Defines the diameter of the carrier web, after which a pre-warning for the rewinder is avti-vated. The following message appears "Rewinder almost full".
Defines the diameter of the carrier web, after which the labeler stops. The following mes-sage appears "Rewinder full".
Defines the value for the motor current, after which the following message appears "Load approaching the upper limit".

Parameter for activating contour mode. When the parameter is activated, the two parameters "Start contour" and "Stop contour" are displayed in the configuration menu. At the same time, the "Ramp" parameter is ignored.
Determines the number of encoder pulses per millimeter of label path and synchronizes an optional printer at the AUX socket.
This Parameter is used to set the communication with different PLC versions.
This parameter is used to set the distance (duration) in splice mode. The label web is ad-vanced with the reduced speed specified in parameter 071. 0 - 9999. Adjusting the value in [mm]

This parameter is only used if parameter 070 is active. It is used to reduce reduce the speed in the slice mode and is calculated on the basis of the current speed. 10 - 100. Adjusting the value in [%]

This parameter is only used for alternating operation and defines the transfer reserve that is still to be dispensed in alternating operation. Must be less than or equal to Par.25 RestLowLabel. 0.0 – 90.0. Adjusting the value in [m]
Offset setting for operation with rotary encoder. The feed rate of the dispenser is factor Par.73 x encoder speed. 20.0 - 500.0. Adjusting the value in [%].

Setting of the start ramp setting in m/s2. If the value is 0, the ramp length is used to calcu-late the acceleration. The stop ramp is set exactly as before via the ratio to the start ramp. 0.0 - 90.0. In [m/s2]
Setting of a speed offset in 1/10 m/min. Only applies to the internal speed. Parameter 073 can be used in encoder mode. -20.0 - 20.0. in [%]
Determines whether the material transport error "Materialtransportoffen" is to be output. The signal for the error must be applied to X22.4. 0 = Off. 1 = Error at 24V. 2 = Error at 0V.

Offset setting of the encoder speed for the internal calculation of Alpha HSM, e.g. for win-ding tape operation and ZDT application. Alpha HSM must calculate with baseband speed for the function of the ZDT, but dispenses with encoder speed from the winding belt. 20.0 - 500.0. In [%]
